.SH "NAME"
Catalyst::Model::Factory \- use a plain class as a Catalyst model,
instantiating it every time it is requested
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
This module works just like
Catalyst::Model::Adaptor, except that a
fresh instance of your adapted class is created every time it is
requested via \f(CW\*(C`$c\->model\*(C'\fR.
.SH "CUSTOMIZING"
.IX Header "CUSTOMIZING"
You can customize your subclass just like
Catalyst::Model::Adaptor.  Instead of
\&\f(CW$app\fR, though, you'll get \f(CW$c\fR, the current request context.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
These methods are called by Catalyst, not by you:
.SS "\s-1COMPONENT\s0"
.IX Subsection "COMPONENT"
Load your class
.SS "\s-1ACCEPT_CONTEXT\s0"
.IX Subsection "ACCEPT_CONTEXT"
Create an instance of your class and return it.
